  "prompt": "How do you fix a Bissell carpet cleaner that won't spray water?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to troubleshoot a Bissell carpet cleaner that won't spray water:\n\n1. Check the water tank\n- Ensure it's properly filled\n- Confirm it's correctly seated and locked into place\n- Clean the tank if there's any debris or buildup\n\n2. Inspect the solution line\n- Check for any kinks or blockages in the hose\n- Disconnect and clear any potential clogs\n- Ensure connections are tight and secure\n\n3. Clean the spray nozzles\n- Remove and clean spray nozzles\n- Use a small brush or pin to clear any blockages\n- Rinse thoroughly\n\n4. Check the pump\n- Verify the pump is functioning correctly\n- Listen for unusual sounds when operating\n- Ensure electrical connections are secure\n\n5. Examine the belt\n- Make sure the belt is not broken or loose\n- Replace if it appears worn or damaged\n\n6. Verify power and settings\n- Confirm the machine is plugged in\n- Check that it's turned on and set to the correct mode\n- Ensure you're pressing the trigger to release solution\n\nIf these steps don't resolve the issue, contact Bissell customer support or consider professional repair.",
